HEADWORD: Zamindar
<hw>Zam`in*dar"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Hind.
<ets>zem⟦imac⟧nd⟦amac⟧r</ets>, <ets>zam⟦imac⟧nd⟦amac⟧r</ets>, a
landholder, Per. <ets>zam⟦imac⟧nd⟦amac⟧r</ets>; <ets>zam⟦imac⟧n</ets>
land <ets>d⟦amac⟧r</ets> holding.]</ety> <def>A landowner; also, a
collector of land revenue; now, usually, a kind of feudatory recognized
as an actual proprietor so long as he pays to the government a certain
fixed revenue.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>zemindar</asp>.]</altsp>
<mark>[India]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

